<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
  "Operators busy -> leave a voicemail" bin.

  Paste into a Telnyx TeXML Bin (Voice -> TeXML -> Create TeXML Bin). Use it as
  the TeXML Application Failover URL, or as a department's destination, so callers
  can always leave a message even when your app/agents are unavailable.

  Telnyx records the message and STORES it on Telnyx automatically — you can find
  every recording in Mission Control -> Reporting -> Recordings, fetch them via the
  Recordings API, or have them pushed to recordingStatusCallback below (your app
  logs the URL at /texml/recording). The recording happens whether or not that
  callback succeeds, so voicemails are never lost.

  Replace YOUR_BASE_URL with your public host (e.g. ivr.yourdomain.com). If you
  don't want the callback, delete the recordingStatusCallback attribute entirely —
  recordings still land in the Telnyx portal.
-->
<Response>
  <Say voice="Polly.Joanna-Neural">Hi! All of our phone operators are busy right now. Please leave a voicemail after the beep and we will hear it and get back to you. Press the pound key when you are finished.</Say>
  <Record maxLength="180"
          finishOnKey="#"
          playBeep="true"
          recordingStatusCallback="https://YOUR_BASE_URL/texml/recording" />
  <Say voice="Polly.Joanna-Neural">Thank you. We have your message. Goodbye.</Say>
  <Hangup/>
</Response>
